50|$|Chromatic {{adaptation}} is a {{prime example}} for the case that two different stimuli with thereby different XYZ <b>tristimulus</b> <b>values</b> create an identical color appearance. If the color temperature of the illuminating light source changes, so do the spectral power distribution and thereby the XYZ <b>tristimulus</b> <b>values</b> of the light reflected from the white paper; the color appearance, however, stays the same (white).|$|R
