50|$|The basic {{challenge}} for any color appearance model is that human color perception {{does not work}} in terms of XYZ <b>tristimulus</b> <b>values,</b> {{but in terms of}} appearance parameters (hue, lightness, brightness, chroma, colorfulness and saturation). So any color appearance model needs to provide transformations (which factor in viewing conditions) from the XYZ <b>tristimulus</b> <b>values</b> to these appearance parameters (at least hue, lightness and chroma).|$|R
