25|$|The CIE XYZ {{color space}} {{encompasses}} all color sensations that are visible {{to a person}} with average eyesight. That is why CIE XYZ (<b>Tristimulus</b> <b>values)</b> is a device-invariant representation of color. It serves as a standard reference against which many other color spaces are defined. A set of color-matching functions, like the spectral sensitivity curves of the LMS color space, but not restricted to non-negative sensitivities, associates physically produced light spectra with specific <b>tristimulus</b> <b>values.</b>|$|R
50|$|Metamerism: Wyszecki {{introduced}} the important concept of ‘metameric blacks,’ psychophysical definitions of blacks with <b>tristimulus</b> <b>values</b> 0, 0, 0 that within limits {{can be added}} to a spectral reflectance to form the various possible metamers (with an identical set of <b>tristimulus</b> <b>values)</b> under a given light. With W.S. Stiles he also developed mathematical methods to calculate by various methodologies the number of possible metamers for given chromaticities, peaking at the achromatic colors.|$|R
